WEBVTT

STYLE
::cue(c.color9CD5FF) { color: #9CD5FF; }
::cue(c.colora8c7fa) { color: #a8c7fa; }

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:07.000 line:5% align:middle
<b><c.color9CD5FF>One Pace Premium</c></b>
Keep the project alive: <c.colora8c7fa>ko-fi.com/not6ip</c>

2
00:00:01.520 --> 00:00:03.650
Wealth, fame, power...

3
00:00:03.650 --> 00:00:07.820
Gold Roger, the King of the Pirates, obtained everything the world has to offer.

4
00:00:07.820 --> 00:00:11.660
What he said in his final moments drove countless souls to the seas.

5
00:00:11.660 --> 00:00:13.660
You want my treasure?

6
00:00:13.660 --> 00:00:15.450
Go ahead.

7
00:00:15.450 --> 00:00:16.660
Find it!

8
00:00:16.660 --> 00:00:19.250
Everything is right where I left it!

9
00:00:21.670 --> 00:00:26.380
People set their sights on the Grand Line in pursuit of their dreams.

10
00:00:26.380 --> 00:00:29.630
The world has truly entered the Great Pirate Era!

11
00:00:30.390 --> 00:00:35.640
Come aboard and bring along all your hopes and dreams

12
00:00:35.850 --> 00:00:41.440
I know together we'll find everything we're looking for

13
00:00:41.770 --> 00:00:42.690
One Piece!

14
00:00:47.900 --> 00:00:52.700
Compasses? Not for me. Left them all behind

15
00:00:53.580 --> 00:00:58.500
I'm headed out to sea, with my heart serving as guide

16
00:00:59.330 --> 00:01:04.540
Following the ancient map to the spot marked "X" reveals

17
00:01:04.540 --> 00:01:09.760
Yeah, it's only legendary till someone proves it's real

18
00:01:11.380 --> 00:01:13.710
When the world's got you down,

19
00:01:13.710 --> 00:01:16.850
lean on your crew, they'll turn it around

20
00:01:17.180 --> 00:01:22.190
Their biorhythm will carry you through

21
00:01:22.400 --> 00:01:24.230
We're gonna make the most of it

22
00:01:26.110 --> 00:01:31.400
Come aboard and bring along all your hopes and dreams

23
00:01:31.610 --> 00:01:36.990
I know together we'll find everything we're looking for

24
00:01:37.330 --> 00:01:40.040
Got some change to my name,

25
00:01:40.040 --> 00:01:43.250
and maybe you wanna be my friend?

26
00:01:43.540 --> 00:01:48.130
We are, we are on the cruise!

27
00:01:48.920 --> 00:01:49.760
WE ARE!

28
00:01:50.050 --> 00:01:54.680
<b>You're the Weird Animal</b>

29
00:02:03.810 --> 00:02:06.270
You foolish pirates.

30
00:02:07.270 --> 00:02:10.740
You dare attack the Going Merry,
knowing that it is commandeered

31
00:02:10.740 --> 00:02:14.240
by Captain Usopp
and his invincible pirate fleet?!

32
00:02:15.490 --> 00:02:18.330
All hands on deck! Prepare for battle!

33
00:02:22.790 --> 00:02:26.920
Come on, guys... Would it
really hurt to play along a bit?

34
00:02:26.920 --> 00:02:28.460
It's done!

35
00:02:29.840 --> 00:02:31.710
Look! It's our pirate flag!

36
00:02:31.710 --> 00:02:34.970
We've got four crew members
now that Usopp's joined!

37
00:02:34.970 --> 00:02:37.050
It's time we had our own Jolly Roger!

38
00:02:38.050 --> 00:02:41.020
Is that... supposed to be
our Jolly Roger?

39
00:02:41.770 --> 00:02:43.980
How is it? Cool, right?

40
00:02:43.980 --> 00:02:48.020
A pirate flag is supposed to
be scary, a symbol of death.

41
00:02:48.020 --> 00:02:51.860
I do feel scared, though—
scared of your artwork.

42
00:02:53.360 --> 00:02:55.490
You should have just said something.

43
00:02:55.990 --> 00:02:59.030
Don't forget that I'm famous
for my artistic talent.

44
00:02:59.580 --> 00:03:00.790
Artistic talent?

45
00:03:01.660 --> 00:03:03.910
When it comes to painting,

46
00:03:03.910 --> 00:03:07.210
no one can top the fifty years
I spent graffitiing on walls.

47
00:03:09.790 --> 00:03:12.920
Now, gaze upon
my artistic masterpiece!

48
00:03:12.920 --> 00:03:14.420
Ta-da!

49
00:03:14.420 --> 00:03:16.510
Who said to make it look like you?

50
00:03:20.220 --> 00:03:22.010
Maybe something like this?

51
00:03:22.010 --> 00:03:24.140
Wow, that's pretty good!

52
00:03:24.140 --> 00:03:26.140
Yeah, it looks great. I love it!

53
00:03:26.940 --> 00:03:29.440
So this will be our symbol?

54
00:03:29.440 --> 00:03:32.690
Alright, Usopp!
Let's draw it on the sail too!

55
00:03:32.690 --> 00:03:33.650
You got it!

56
00:03:36.610 --> 00:03:38.740
Alright! All done!

57
00:03:39.950 --> 00:03:43.540
Our pirate ship,
the Going Merry, is finally ready!

58
00:03:45.750 --> 00:03:47.830
Phew! I'm exhausted!

59
00:03:52.710 --> 00:03:54.420
Should we really go this way?

60
00:03:54.420 --> 00:03:56.380
That looks like trouble.

61
00:03:56.760 --> 00:03:57.880
Trouble?

62
00:03:57.880 --> 00:03:59.340
Hold on.

63
00:04:01.100 --> 00:04:02.600
That must be it...

64
00:04:02.600 --> 00:04:04.600
It is! No doubt about it!

65
00:04:04.600 --> 00:04:07.060
Did you see something interesting?

66
00:04:07.940 --> 00:04:09.730
The legendary treasure island.

67
00:04:09.730 --> 00:04:11.610
"Legendary treasure island"?

68
00:04:11.610 --> 00:04:13.070
I've heard about it!

69
00:04:13.070 --> 00:04:16.820
That's right. This island is
famous among pirates.

70
00:04:16.820 --> 00:04:18.570
Many odd rumors surround it.

71
00:04:18.910 --> 00:04:20.490
Odd rumors?

72
00:04:20.820 --> 00:04:25.950
Like, "Whoever comes near this island
will feel the wrath of the gods."

73
00:04:30.750 --> 00:04:32.750
So the rumors are true?

74
00:04:32.750 --> 00:04:34.210
Is this the wrath of the gods?!

75
00:04:34.210 --> 00:04:35.880
Whatever it is, it sounds fun!

76
00:04:35.880 --> 00:04:37.840
Luffy, you don't mean...

77
00:04:37.840 --> 00:04:39.510
He does!

78
00:04:44.640 --> 00:04:47.020
Let's go to the treasure island!

79
00:04:47.020 --> 00:04:48.680
And pull!

80
00:05:29.350 --> 00:05:32.020
Man, I'm hungry.

81
00:05:32.020 --> 00:05:33.940
I'll just sleep.

82
00:05:35.770 --> 00:05:38.650
I'm amazed he can nap
in such a creepy place.

83
00:05:38.650 --> 00:05:40.950
Just what are his nerves made of?

84
00:05:48.830 --> 00:05:50.910
What?! Don't scare me like that!

85
00:05:50.910 --> 00:05:54.670
Ah... you see... I just thought
I'd dance a little to cheer us up a bit!

86
00:05:54.670 --> 00:05:57.550
You see? Like this, see?

87
00:06:00.420 --> 00:06:02.220
Cut that out, Luffy...

88
00:06:10.730 --> 00:06:12.690
Th-This...

89
00:06:16.480 --> 00:06:19.110
Leave this place.

90
00:06:19.110 --> 00:06:19.860
Who's that?!

91
00:06:20.360 --> 00:06:22.450
Leave this place!

92
00:06:22.450 --> 00:06:24.490
Where's that voice coming from?

93
00:06:24.860 --> 00:06:27.490
I am the guardian deity of this island.

94
00:06:27.490 --> 00:06:30.830
Begone from this place at once
if you value your lives!

95
00:06:30.830 --> 00:06:32.580
Guardian deity?

96
00:06:32.580 --> 00:06:34.960
You people are pirates, right?

97
00:06:34.960 --> 00:06:35.670
Yup.

98
00:06:35.670 --> 00:06:37.840
Pirates, huh? Thought so.

99
00:06:37.840 --> 00:06:40.550
Why would a deity ask such a thing?

100
00:06:40.550 --> 00:06:44.300
Listen closely. The moment
you step into this forest,

101
00:06:44.300 --> 00:06:50.640
you will suffer the gods' judgment
and face certain doom, won't you?

102
00:06:50.640 --> 00:06:52.930
How should I know?
Why are you asking me?

103
00:06:52.930 --> 00:06:54.270
Just what is going on?

104
00:06:54.270 --> 00:06:55.900
This guy is kinda weird.

105
00:06:55.900 --> 00:06:58.900
What did you say, straw hat boy?!

106
00:07:05.200 --> 00:07:07.030
What's with this place?

107
00:07:07.030 --> 00:07:12.830
This is what I did to the humans
that came here looking for treasure.

108
00:07:14.040 --> 00:07:16.750
So that means you really are a god?!

109
00:07:17.080 --> 00:07:19.380
A lot of these look really strange.

110
00:07:19.880 --> 00:07:21.250
Is this one a lion?

111
00:07:21.250 --> 00:07:22.920
Isn't it a pig?

112
00:07:24.630 --> 00:07:26.380
Ow! Ow! Ow! Ow!

113
00:07:27.010 --> 00:07:29.510
Wh-What in the world are you?!

114
00:07:29.510 --> 00:07:31.260
I'm a rubber man!

115
00:07:31.260 --> 00:07:32.720
I ate a devil fruit.

116
00:07:32.720 --> 00:07:34.140
A devil fruit?

117
00:07:34.140 --> 00:07:35.430
That's absurd!

118
00:07:35.430 --> 00:07:38.020
I heard about those
back when I was a pirate, but–

119
00:07:38.020 --> 00:07:39.770
"Back when I was a pirate"?

120
00:07:39.770 --> 00:07:43.230
N-No! It's not like I often reminisce
on those times or anything!

121
00:07:43.230 --> 00:07:46.110
You know, let's stop
digging up the past!

122
00:07:46.110 --> 00:07:47.320
What're you saying?

123
00:07:47.320 --> 00:07:48.660
You brought this up.

124
00:07:48.660 --> 00:07:50.950
Are you really a god?

125
00:07:50.950 --> 00:07:54.660
Silence! Leave now or suffer the judgment of the gods!

126
00:08:03.750 --> 00:08:05.260
Not bad, god guy.

127
00:08:05.260 --> 00:08:07.170
H-How are you still standing?

128
00:08:07.170 --> 00:08:08.050
Oh, he's over there?

129
00:08:08.050 --> 00:08:08.840
Don't move!

130
00:08:09.930 --> 00:08:11.350
I said don't move!

131
00:08:15.430 --> 00:08:17.850
Wh... What?! No fair!

132
00:08:17.850 --> 00:08:19.600
You know, god, or whatever you are...

133
00:08:19.600 --> 00:08:21.860
you can't hurt this guy,
even with a pistol.

134
00:08:21.860 --> 00:08:23.820
Still, don't startle me like that.

135
00:08:23.820 --> 00:08:26.570
I-It's a monster!

136
00:08:26.570 --> 00:08:28.070
Hey! There he is!

137
00:08:28.740 --> 00:08:30.870
It was just a pistol after all.

138
00:08:35.490 --> 00:08:36.870
Where'd he go?

139
00:08:41.460 --> 00:08:42.880
What's this?

140
00:08:42.880 --> 00:08:45.250
Is this... the guardian deity?

141
00:08:46.670 --> 00:08:47.760
It moved!

142
00:08:58.060 --> 00:09:00.520
What are you waiting for?!
Lift me back up!

143
00:09:00.520 --> 00:09:01.810
It's a human.

144
00:09:01.810 --> 00:09:03.860
That's so funny! Is he a sponge?

145
00:09:03.860 --> 00:09:07.940
You little... What kind of god
relies on cheap tricks?

146
00:09:07.940 --> 00:09:10.490
Just shut it and stand me back up!

147
00:09:10.490 --> 00:09:12.490
So bossy after you fell!

148
00:09:14.830 --> 00:09:16.950
Alright, that should do it.

149
00:09:16.990 --> 00:09:20.660
<b>Gaimon
Inhabitant of the Island</b>

150
00:09:21.710 --> 00:09:24.130
You're pretty popular here, god guy.

151
00:09:24.130 --> 00:09:29.470
So you've been using these animals
to drive any intruders off the island.

152
00:09:29.920 --> 00:09:33.010
But, um, I've never seen a guy
living in a treasure chest before.

153
00:09:33.010 --> 00:09:35.260
Did your family
treasure you that much?

154
00:09:35.260 --> 00:09:38.680
Yes. Ever since I was a child,
they'd express their love for me by...

155
00:09:38.680 --> 00:09:40.430
As if!

156
00:09:40.430 --> 00:09:43.270
I can't get out of this box!
I'm trapped!

157
00:09:43.270 --> 00:09:48.110
I've been on this island for twenty years
all alone and stuck in this chest!

158
00:09:48.610 --> 00:09:49.820
Twenty years?!

159
00:09:57.660 --> 00:10:00.660
You've been here by yourself
for twenty years?

160
00:10:00.660 --> 00:10:04.630
Just look at my hair and my beard.
Even my eyebrows have connected.

161
00:10:05.080 --> 00:10:08.300
This is my first conversation
with anybody in two decades.

162
00:10:08.630 --> 00:10:11.050
Do you understand
how lonely it's been?

163
00:10:12.170 --> 00:10:13.010
Sounds dumb.

164
00:10:13.010 --> 00:10:14.220
What did you say?!

165
00:10:16.720 --> 00:10:18.850
Oh, so that's where you were.

166
00:10:18.850 --> 00:10:22.230
You're telling us you slept
through all that commotion?

167
00:10:31.530 --> 00:10:33.490
Huh?! What the hell is that?!

168
00:10:33.490 --> 00:10:35.110
Now you notice?

169
00:10:35.110 --> 00:10:37.200
He's a guy stuck in a treasure chest.

170
00:10:37.200 --> 00:10:39.450
What?! His parents
treasured him that much?!

171
00:10:39.450 --> 00:10:42.910
Yes. Ever since I was a child,
they'd express their love for me by...

172
00:10:42.910 --> 00:10:44.290
As if!

173
00:10:44.290 --> 00:10:46.290
It wasn't funny the first time!

174
00:10:46.290 --> 00:10:47.590
Zoro, gimme a hand.

175
00:10:47.590 --> 00:10:50.250
Ow! Ow! What are you doing?!

176
00:10:50.250 --> 00:10:53.840
Stop it! You'll rip my head off!

177
00:10:53.840 --> 00:10:56.260
Whew... He really can't get out!

178
00:10:56.260 --> 00:10:57.640
What did you expect?!

179
00:10:57.640 --> 00:11:00.260
I haven't gotten any exercise in years.

180
00:11:00.260 --> 00:11:03.100
My body barely even fits in this box.

181
00:11:03.100 --> 00:11:06.060
In fact, this box is the only thing
holding me together!

182
00:11:06.060 --> 00:11:07.900
He sure talks a lot.

183
00:11:09.060 --> 00:11:11.820
Anyway, what's the story
behind your little crew?

184
00:11:11.820 --> 00:11:15.360
You're nothing at all like
the other pirates that came here.

185
00:11:16.490 --> 00:11:17.490
I'm Luffy!

186
00:11:17.490 --> 00:11:21.120
I'm gonna be the Pirate King
and find the One Piece!

187
00:11:21.120 --> 00:11:22.790
The One Piece?!

188
00:11:22.790 --> 00:11:26.500
You don't actually mean
to enter the Grand Line, do you?!

189
00:11:26.500 --> 00:11:28.130
I have a map to get there and all!

190
00:11:29.000 --> 00:11:31.000
Don't underestimate that place!

191
00:11:31.000 --> 00:11:33.380
It'll cause you hell or be your death!

192
00:11:33.380 --> 00:11:38.390
A long time ago, I saw a crew of pirates
return from the Grand Line.

193
00:11:38.390 --> 00:11:42.010
They looked like walking corpses,
utterly soulless.

194
00:11:42.010 --> 00:11:46.480
But whatever they had encountered,
it must have been terrifying.

195
00:11:46.480 --> 00:11:49.060
None of them spoke a single word.

196
00:11:50.150 --> 00:11:53.480
That aside, with so many rumors
surrounding the One Piece,

197
00:11:53.480 --> 00:11:55.860
there's no way of knowing
what to believe.

198
00:11:56.200 --> 00:11:59.410
It's been over two decades
since the dawn of the Great Pirate Era.

199
00:11:59.410 --> 00:12:03.830
And now, the One Piece is beyond legend,
a dream within a dream.

200
00:12:06.750 --> 00:12:09.380
So, where on there is the Grand Line?

201
00:12:09.380 --> 00:12:10.250
No idea...

202
00:12:10.250 --> 00:12:12.130
You don't know, sponge guy?

203
00:12:12.130 --> 00:12:14.340
These sea charts
don't mean a thing to me.

204
00:12:14.340 --> 00:12:16.130
Yeah. Same here.

205
00:12:17.470 --> 00:12:19.930
You're really not acting
like a pirate here.

206
00:12:20.340 --> 00:12:23.220
In any case, even if you
entered the Grand Line,

207
00:12:23.220 --> 00:12:26.850
it'd be best to just grab as much
treasure as possible and bounce.

208
00:12:26.850 --> 00:12:29.810
Oh, I'll find the One Piece.
I'm pretty lucky.

209
00:12:30.400 --> 00:12:32.650
I wonder how you stay so confident.

210
00:12:32.980 --> 00:12:35.610
Just watch, I'll find it for sure!

211
00:12:35.610 --> 00:12:37.190
Oh, dear...

212
00:12:39.450 --> 00:12:40.530
That look...

213
00:12:41.450 --> 00:12:45.410
Your face is just like mine was.
It's as if we're twins.

214
00:12:45.410 --> 00:12:47.580
Have you seen yourself recently?

215
00:12:48.080 --> 00:12:49.460
I understand how you feel.

216
00:12:49.460 --> 00:12:51.460
One day, we would reach our dreams.

217
00:12:51.460 --> 00:12:53.840
That's what we always believed!

218
00:12:54.460 --> 00:12:55.670
"We"?

219
00:12:55.670 --> 00:12:59.050
We'd happily put our lives on the line
in search of treasure.

220
00:12:59.050 --> 00:13:02.890
That burning passion
turned my life upside-down.

221
00:13:02.890 --> 00:13:04.390
H-Hold on, just what–

222
00:13:04.390 --> 00:13:07.560
It all started twenty years ago.

223
00:13:07.560 --> 00:13:10.810
My pirate crewmates and I
made landfall on this island.

224
00:13:12.230 --> 00:13:15.730
We were searching for the treasure
that was said to lie hidden here.

225
00:13:19.280 --> 00:13:23.240
All 200 of us have been searching
this island for a full month now...

226
00:13:23.870 --> 00:13:26.830
but this empty chest was
the only thing we found!

227
00:13:27.290 --> 00:13:28.830
Men, get ready to leave!

228
00:13:28.830 --> 00:13:29.830
– Yeah!
– You got it!

229
00:13:32.420 --> 00:13:34.840
What are you waiting for,
Gaimon? We're leaving.

230
00:13:34.840 --> 00:13:36.000
Right.

231
00:13:34.880 --> 00:13:36.960
<b>Gaimon
(Twenty Years Ago)</b>

232
00:13:38.840 --> 00:13:41.970
I wonder if anybody
ever searched up there.

233
00:13:41.970 --> 00:13:44.850
The captain stayed around here
the whole month, but...

234
00:13:47.600 --> 00:13:49.600
let's make sure one last time.

235
00:13:56.020 --> 00:13:58.570
I couldn't believe my own eyes.

236
00:13:59.030 --> 00:14:01.700
I... I found it! That's where it was!

237
00:14:01.700 --> 00:14:04.490
Hey! Everyone!

238
00:14:14.290 --> 00:14:16.750
That was the moment
I got stuck in this box.

239
00:14:17.920 --> 00:14:21.380
When I came to,
my crewmates were long gone.

240
00:14:22.970 --> 00:14:24.550
I messed up!

241
00:14:25.840 --> 00:14:27.220
Wait.

242
00:14:27.220 --> 00:14:30.560
Doesn't this mean
that the treasure is all mine now?

243
00:14:32.060 --> 00:14:34.060
I can't climb up like this!

244
00:14:34.060 --> 00:14:37.310
I can't get out! I'm stuck, dammit!

245
00:14:43.200 --> 00:14:44.740
Ever since that day,

246
00:14:44.740 --> 00:14:49.910
I couldn't get my mind
off that treasure for even a second.

247
00:14:49.910 --> 00:14:53.790
Countless pirates came to
this island looking for riches,

248
00:14:53.790 --> 00:14:56.670
but I scared them all off
with the help of my animal friends.

249
00:14:56.670 --> 00:15:02.010
For twenty years, I've
protected the treasure this way.

250
00:15:02.590 --> 00:15:03.920
It belongs to me!

251
00:15:03.920 --> 00:15:05.680
Yup, no doubt about it.

252
00:15:05.680 --> 00:15:07.140
That treasure is yours.

253
00:15:07.140 --> 00:15:08.970
Leave it to us, Gaimon.

254
00:15:08.970 --> 00:15:12.350
We'll get that treasure for you.

255
00:15:13.180 --> 00:15:14.560
R-Really?!

256
00:15:13.680 --> 00:15:14.560
Yeah.

257
00:15:14.890 --> 00:15:15.810
Is she...

258
00:15:16.190 --> 00:15:19.110
Aren't you a thief
who steals from pirates?

259
00:15:19.110 --> 00:15:20.270
Don't be rude!

260
00:15:20.900 --> 00:15:23.280
I do have some integrity, you know.

261
00:15:47.550 --> 00:15:48.760
This is it, huh?

262
00:15:48.760 --> 00:15:51.680
It's been a while
since I've been here, too.

263
00:15:55.390 --> 00:15:57.770
So it's finally time.

264
00:15:57.770 --> 00:15:58.940
Today is a great day.

265
00:15:58.940 --> 00:16:00.440
It's up to you now, Straw Hat.

266
00:16:00.440 --> 00:16:01.060
Alright!

267
00:16:01.060 --> 00:16:02.520
Gum-Gum...

268
00:16:06.150 --> 00:16:09.280
Rocket!

269
00:16:09.870 --> 00:16:12.120
Woo-hoo!

270
00:16:18.290 --> 00:16:20.130
And? Is it there?

271
00:16:25.630 --> 00:16:28.090
It is! Five treasure chests!

272
00:16:28.090 --> 00:16:29.840
I-I did it!

273
00:16:32.430 --> 00:16:36.180
I finally got my treasure! I got it!

274
00:16:36.180 --> 00:16:37.850
Can you throw it down here?

275
00:16:37.850 --> 00:16:40.940
Throw me my treasure! Hurry up!

276
00:16:40.940 --> 00:16:41.690
I don't wanna.

277
00:16:41.690 --> 00:16:42.980
What?!

278
00:16:44.320 --> 00:16:47.030
I don't wanna give it to you.

279
00:16:47.030 --> 00:16:48.820
What are you saying?

280
00:16:48.820 --> 00:16:50.360
Stop those stupid jokes!

281
00:16:55.450 --> 00:16:57.410
Cut it out, Luffy!

282
00:16:57.410 --> 00:16:58.790
Don't worry about it.

283
00:16:59.960 --> 00:17:01.120
It's alright.

284
00:17:01.120 --> 00:17:02.210
It's not alright!

285
00:17:02.210 --> 00:17:06.420
Yeah, this is the treasure you've been
guarding for twenty years!

286
00:17:07.840 --> 00:17:10.050
Straw Hat, you're...

287
00:17:10.050 --> 00:17:12.390
you're a great guy.

288
00:17:13.180 --> 00:17:14.600
What do you mean?

289
00:17:15.430 --> 00:17:19.770
I've always had this slight suspicion
in the back of my mind.

290
00:17:19.770 --> 00:17:22.940
But I've tried my best
not to think about it.

291
00:17:24.270 --> 00:17:26.320
They're empty, aren't they?

292
00:17:28.610 --> 00:17:29.820
Yeah.

293
00:17:29.820 --> 00:17:31.410
All of them.

294
00:17:31.410 --> 00:17:32.570
That's terrible...

295
00:17:32.570 --> 00:17:36.990
The treasure he guarded for twenty
years was just some empty boxes...

296
00:17:36.990 --> 00:17:41.710
It happens all the time when treasures
have maps leading to them.

297
00:17:42.080 --> 00:17:45.170
You follow the map,
but the loot's already gone.

298
00:17:45.170 --> 00:17:48.920
That's what makes treasure hunting
so brutal for pirates.

299
00:17:49.420 --> 00:17:53.760
You could spend a lifetime searching
and still not reach it.

300
00:17:53.760 --> 00:17:56.180
Countless pirates
have suffered that fate.

301
00:17:58.890 --> 00:18:01.390
Well, look on the bright side, sponge guy.

302
00:18:01.390 --> 00:18:03.650
You're lucky we came here
after twenty years.

303
00:18:03.980 --> 00:18:06.940
If you had to wait another thirty,
you could've died.

304
00:18:07.980 --> 00:18:09.320
Straw Hat...

305
00:18:09.320 --> 00:18:10.240
Luffy...

306
00:18:10.240 --> 00:18:11.320
He's...

307
00:18:11.320 --> 00:18:13.450
After an embarrassment like this,

308
00:18:13.450 --> 00:18:15.780
there's no harm in going for the One Piece.

309
00:18:15.780 --> 00:18:18.410
Come with us and be a pirate again!

310
00:18:18.410 --> 00:18:22.540
You'd really invite me?

311
00:18:23.420 --> 00:18:25.380
Up until now,

312
00:18:25.380 --> 00:18:28.380
no one gave me a second glance,
let alone talked to me.

313
00:18:29.050 --> 00:18:32.340
How long has it been
since I could trust somebody?

314
00:18:38.810 --> 00:18:40.680
Thank you.

315
00:18:51.820 --> 00:18:54.820
You're really staying
on this island, sponge guy?

316
00:18:54.820 --> 00:18:56.160
Yeah, Straw Hat.

317
00:18:56.160 --> 00:19:00.120
Even if the treasure's not here,
there's something else I want to protect.

318
00:19:00.120 --> 00:19:01.240
Huh?

319
00:19:01.240 --> 00:19:02.620
Something else?

320
00:19:04.540 --> 00:19:08.590
I've lived with them through
thick and thin for twenty years.

321
00:19:08.590 --> 00:19:10.840
There's no way I'd abandon them.

322
00:19:18.510 --> 00:19:23.180
Now that I know there's no treasure,
I finally feel like I'm free.

323
00:19:23.180 --> 00:19:26.560
From now on,
I can truly live my own life.

324
00:19:26.560 --> 00:19:29.520
And you know, I've kind of grown
to like living in a box.

325
00:19:29.520 --> 00:19:31.530
I see. That's too bad.

326
00:19:31.530 --> 00:19:33.280
You're a cool guy.

327
00:19:33.280 --> 00:19:35.530
So these weird animals
are your real friends.

328
00:19:36.070 --> 00:19:38.280
But you're the weirdest
animal of them all.

329
00:19:38.280 --> 00:19:39.450
What?!

330
00:19:49.210 --> 00:19:50.590
Bye-bye!

331
00:19:50.590 --> 00:19:52.670
Take care!

332
00:19:52.670 --> 00:19:54.510
Goodbye!

333
00:19:57.340 --> 00:19:58.840
Straw Hat...

334
00:19:58.840 --> 00:20:02.350
do your best to achieve your dreams.
For my sake, too.

335
00:20:02.760 --> 00:20:05.350
I'm sure you can find it.

336
00:20:05.850 --> 00:20:08.190
The legendary treasure, One Piece.

337
00:20:10.230 --> 00:20:15.900
And then, make the world your own!

338
00:20:22.120 --> 00:20:28.980
As a kid, I had a dream of a dazzling treasure

339
00:20:29.180 --> 00:20:36.000
I had a map in my head that I knew would lead me

340
00:20:36.250 --> 00:20:43.100
Charted a course all on my own, so nobody would beat me

341
00:20:43.220 --> 00:20:50.360
The promised land was in my hand, drew a line in the sand

342
00:20:53.060 --> 00:20:55.740
Look where I am

343
00:20:57.970 --> 00:21:04.150
My one ambition's slipping right through my hands

344
00:21:04.490 --> 00:21:11.420
But if the world ever changes I'll call out your name

345
00:21:11.580 --> 00:21:18.500
We could return to a time when our lives were still the same

346
00:21:18.630 --> 00:21:25.630
Take me to the place where memories remain

347
00:21:25.730 --> 00:21:31.500
Please don't ever let them fade
